RACE.RACE_TEXT: Minnesota Oaks CANTERBURY PARK RACE 1 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 93. Stakes Purse 100000. FOR FILLIES, THREE YEARS OLD WHICH ARE REGISTERED MINNESOTA BREDS. $250 to nominate by Saturday, April 1. Late nomination fee: $750 by Thursday, June 1. $500 to enter, $500 additional to start. Supplemental nominations of $2,000 will be accepted at time of entry which shall include all fees. $100,000 Guaranteed (Plus $10,000 from the Minnesota Breeders Fund for horses Sired & Foaled in Minnesota) of which $60,000 to the owner of the winner. All other purse monies paid corresponding with purse schedule in the Condition Book. Weight: 122 lbs. Maidens allowed 5 lbs. Starters to be named through the entry box by the usual time of closing. The Minnesota Oaks will be limited to fourteen (14) starters. High weights on the scale will be preferred (winners prefer red). Total earnings will be used in determining the order of preference of horses assigned equal weights. Failure to draw into the race will result in a refund of the entry fee. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner. The final purse will be red
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THUNDERS ROCKNROLL gained command immediately after the start, had a ground saving journey, and shook clear in the homestretch for a gate to wire score. CUPIDS CRUSH broke alertly and trekked the two path while pressing the pacesetter through the opening half, was on the heels of leader at upper stretch from a three path position, veered out near the eighth pole, and finished a clear second but was no contest for tough runaway winner. LOVER GIRL settled into mid pack and took a three wide journey through the opening half, chased the pacesetting duo while maintaining the three path route, and proved best of rest behind that top pair. CHECKCASHINGCONNIE travelled widest of all through the opening bend, gave chase from mid pack along the backstretch, and steadily lost ground to front runners in closing half. ANA tucked to the inside to save ground shortly after the start, trekked the inside along the backstretch, and steadily faded in closing strides.

ENTRY.NAME: Thunders Rocknroll
ENTRY.COMMENT: gate to wire, unchallenged

ENTRY.NAME: Cupids Crush
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed two path, three path upper, hooked toughie, clear second

ENTRY.NAME: Lover Girl
ENTRY.COMMENT: three wide journey, not near top duo

ENTRY.NAME: Checkcashingconnie
ENTRY.OWNER: Robertson Hugh H Mentz John and Larson Jeff
ENTRY.COMMENT: wide early, lost ground in the latter half

ENTRY.NAME: Ana
ENTRY.COMMENT: tucked, chased, steadily faded

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 2 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 62. Maiden Special Weight Purse 27000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 118 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: XTREME SMOKE SHOW stalked the early pacesetter from a three wide pose, trekked three wide around the turn, had a slight advantage at upper stretch, drifted in near the eighth pole, and just held off the rallying rival for the score. TAPITURE'S LADY showed reserve in early strides, took an inside track around the bend, then rallied superbly in homestretch to just miss the victory. SHY SHY pressed the early pace from a two path pose, was on even terms for lead between rivals at upper stretch, was forced to change lane nearing the eighth pole, then was nipped at wire for place honors by rallying foe. CRESSONS LIL CHARM hustled from the start and gained first command, had a slight advantage as the inner rival of three abreast at conclusion of backstretch, was headed nearing the quarter pole, then angled out inside the three sixteenths pole and weakened in the final furlong. MISS SILVER settled into mid pack along the backstretch and through the bend, swung wide at upper stretch, and lacked a needed rally. SWEET GETAWAY was unhurried, trailed the field from outset and failed to menace.

ENTRY.NAME: Cressons Lil Charm
ENTRY.COMMENT: led inside, angled out three sixteenths, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Shy Shy
ENTRY.COMMENT: between, forced to change lane eighth pole, nipped for place

ENTRY.NAME: Miss Silver
ENTRY.COMMENT: mid pack, swung wide upper, no late bid

ENTRY.NAME: Sweet Getaway
ENTRY.COMMENT: unhurried, trailed

ENTRY.NAME: Tapiture's Lady
ENTRY.COMMENT: reserved, incredible rally, just missed

ENTRY.NAME: Xtreme Smoke Show
ENTRY.COMMENT: three wide, drifted in eight pole, just held

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOING AT IT hustled from outset and gained first command, took a two path journey through the opening half, tucked to inside around the closing bend, and shook clear in final furlong for a gate to wire score. CLASS COMPOUNDS pressed the pacesetter through the opening half from an inside stance, was within striking distance at upper stretch, and finished a clear second but was no match for winner in final furlong. CHARISMO settled into second flight, lost ground to front runners along backstretch, swung widest at upper stretch and finished willingly to earn the show. JUST BECAUSE came away alertly, trekked three wide through the opening bend, led the second flight along the backstretch, and weakened in crucial stages of contest. HE'S CONNECTED established a ground saving stance shortly after the start, settled into a back rated position and failed to factor. FOREVER INDIAN rated four wide around the opening bend, trailed the field along the backstretch, tucked to save ground late, and was no factor.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHE'S MY WARRIOR rushed from outset to lead the field at first call, travelled the inside line throughout, and never relished command for a wire to wire victory. IT'S HER TIME hustled from outset and forced the pace issue from a two path stance all the way, but was outdueled in final furlong and had to settle for place honors. MOLLY'S ANGEL showed reserve in early strides, advanced to second flight along the backstretch, rated two wide from a three path pose at upper stretch, engaged in a stretch duel behind the lead duo, and bested that rival to secure the show. CHARLIE'S PENNY trekked three wide through the opening bend, gave chase from second flight along the backstretch, saved ground at upper stretch, then was outdueled in final furlong for the show honors. GYPSY REWARD established an inside stance shortly after the start, rated back, nd failed to menace. START SINGING steadily faded in closing stages after settling in between rivals in the early going and losing ground to front runners at the midway point.

FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR MINNESOTA BRED WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the turf, two-year-old races will be run at 6 and 1/2 furlongs and races for three-year-olds and up will be run at a distance of 1 mile on the main track.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROYALS' LIL DIVA lunged at the break, rushed up to two wide through the opening turn, gained command near the five sixteenths pole, shook off all challengers near the eighth pole, and held on for the score. JEWEL AZUL showed reserve through the opening half, advanced on the front runner with a three wide move around the closing bend, rated widest of all at upper stretch, and rallied mildly to procure the place but could not catch the winner in the end. CURIOUS INJI flashed early foot and led the field into the closing bend from an inside position before eclipsing in the crucial portion of contest. LADY CLARE tucked to inside shortly after the start, saved ground throughout, and faded in closing stages.
